# Deterministic-first (S0)

Before an agent turn for routing, validation, dashboard, verify, or autopilot readiness:

1. Check if `scripts/` already performs the step (`route-tier.py`, `validate-workflow.py`, `automation/check-pipeline-blocked.py`, `sync-state.py`, `generate-dashboard.py`, `headless-verify.py`, `verify-router.py`, `update-staleness.py`, `new-task-card.py`, lane scripts, `run-local-pipeline.py`).
2. Run the script; use its output instead of re-deriving state in the LLM.
3. Only use the conductor LLM for merge, gates, and orchestration after S0 output is available.

Workers (subagents) should not run clerical scripts that update journal/state—conductor runs S0 or approves script output, then dual-writes.
